SESSION 3: HTML IMAGES, LINKS & MARQUEE

1. Images in HTML

- Tag: <img>
- Syntax: <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description" width="300" height="200">
- Attributes:
    * src → image path or URL
    * alt → description if image not displayed
    * width → width of image
    * height → height of image

Example:

<img src="logo.png" alt="My Logo" width="200" height="100">

---

2. Links in HTML

- Tag: <a>
- Syntax: <a href="url">Link Text</a>
- Attributes:
    * href → URL to navigate
    * target → "_blank" to open in new tab

Examples:

<a href="https://www.google.com">Visit Google</a>
<a href="about.html" target="_blank">Open About Page</a>

---

3. Mail & Telephone Links

- Email link: <a href="mailto:example@gmail.com">Email Me</a>
- Phone link: <a href="tel:+911234567890">Call Me</a>

---

4. Marquee Tag (Scrolling Text)

- Tag: <marquee> (Note: Deprecated in HTML5, but still works)
- Attributes:
    * direction → left, right, up, down
    * scrollamount → speed of scrolling
    * behavior → scroll, slide, alternate

Example:

<marquee direction="left" scrollamount="5">Welcome to My Website</marquee>

---

5. Practice Tasks:

1. Add an image of your choice with proper width, height, and alt text.
2. Create links to Google, YouTube, and a local HTML page.
3. Add a scrolling marquee with a welcome message.
4. Create email and telephone links.
5. Try changing marquee direction and speed.

